        <div class="pitch">
          <h2>Live Video-Streaming in Android</h2>
          <p>
            With the <a target="_blank" href="https://github.com/cine-io/cineio-broadcast-android">cine.io Android SDK</a>,

            you can publish live RTMP streams right from your Android-powered
            phone or tablet. The h.264 and AAC encoding happens in a hardware-
            accelerated way, so you don't need to worry about battery life.
            Our backend handles the conversion to HLS for consumption on any
            compatible device. Write your code in Java as you normally would.

          </p>

          <h2>Video-Conferencing in Android</h2>
          <p>
            With the <a target="_blank" href="https://github.com/cine-io/cineio-peer-android">cine.io Peer Android SDK</a>,
            you can make and receive calls or join group conferences using
            WebRTC from your Android-powered phone or tablet. We handle all of
            the signaling and identification in a secure and seamless way.
            Write your code in Java as your normally would.
          </p>

        </div>
